<article>
    <h1>Banks here rais&#xAD;ing their game</h1>
    <h2>Bet&#xAD;ter re&#xAD;wards re&#xAD;demp&#xAD;tion sys&#xAD;tems, dig&#xAD;i&#xAD;tal wealth man&#xAD;age&#xAD;ment prod&#xAD;ucts and mer&#xAD;chant tie-ups in pipe&#xAD;line</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210109/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-09"><time>2021-01-09</time></a>
        - <span>BUSINESS</span>
        - <span role="byline">Prisca Ang prisang@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>Con­sumers can ex­pect a wider va­ri­ety of dig­i­tal pay­ment ser­vices this year as tra­di­tional play­ers en­hance their of­fer­ings amid greater com­pe­ti­tion in the bank­ing sec­tor.</p>
    <p>DBS Bank, OCBC Bank and UOB plan to roll out more per­son­alised con­tent, strengthen their fo­cus on part­ner­ships and make the pay­ment jour­ney more seam­less for users.</p>
    <p>On the cards are im­proved re­wards re­demp­tion sys­tems, dig­i­tal wealth man­age­ment prod­ucts and tie-ups with mer­chants in ar­eas like daily es­sen­tials and de­liv­er­ies.</p>
    <p>These ini­tia­tives are part of the banks’ strate­gies to grow the num­ber of users on their e-wal­let, pay­ment and mo­bile bank­ing apps, even as the com­pe­ti­tion hots up with the lib­er­al­i­sa­tion of Sin­ga­pore’s bank­ing in­dus­try.</p>
    <p>Pay­ment rails PayNow and Fast (Fast And Se­cure Trans­fers) will open up to el­i­gi­ble non-bank fi­nan­cial in­sti­tu­tions such as Grab Fi­nan­cial Group and dig­i­tal pay­ment start-up MatchMove from next month, mak­ing it eas­ier for con­sumers to trans­fer funds from their bank ac­counts to mo­bile wal­lets, and be­tween such e-wal­lets.</p>
    <p>In ad­di­tion, con­sumers will be able to ac­cess more non-tra­di­tional bank­ing ser­vices through the four new dig­i­tal banks open­ing from early next year.</p>
    <p>With the Sin­ga­pore Fi­nan­cial Data Ex­change, or SGFinDex, un­veiled last month, it is now eas­ier too for Sin­ga­pore­ans to man­age their fi­nances as they can view their funds and in­vest­ments on a sin­gle on­line plat­form, in­stead of hav­ing to visit each bank’s or gov­ern­ment agency’s web­site.</p>
    <p>The Straits Times finds out how lo­cal banks are ramp­ing up their ef­forts amid these changes.</p>

